CVE-2018-15919.summary: Remotely observable behaviour in auth-gss2.c in OpenSSH through 7.8 could be used by remote attackers to detect existence of users on a target system when GSS2 is in use. NOTE: the discoverer states 'We understand that the OpenSSH developers do not want to treat such a username enumeration (or "oracle") as a vulnerability.'

CVE-2018-15473.summary: OpenSSH through 7.7 is prone to a user enumeration vulnerability due to not delaying bailout for an invalid authenticating user until after the packet containing the request has been fully parsed, related to auth2-gss.c, auth2-hostbased.c, and auth2-pubkey.c.

CVE-2017-15906.summary: The process_open function in sftp-server.c in OpenSSH before 7.6 does not properly prevent write operations in readonly mode, which allows attackers to create zero-length files.

QUALITY & LUXURY

DOWN TO A TEE

3 Abbotsford Place is a luxury self catering holiday home in St Andrews offering a warm welcome in the finest Scottish hospitality.

Abbotsford is a traditional 19th century cottage less than a five minute walk from the R&A and the Old Course, set in a small secluded terrace with private tranquil green and off street parking away from the bustle of North Street. The accommodation has been comfortably furnished to a high standard in a contemporary style over three floors.

The holiday accommodation has been designed with your comfort as a priority.

Abbotsford has four double bedrooms which can be arranged as twins or doubles to our guests requirements each with own bath or shower room (three being en-suite) with a fifth shower room on the ground floor.

Luxury self catering

The property has undergone a complete renovation during the autumn/winter 2011/12

Golf holidays

Golf has been played on the Links at St Andrews since around 1400AD.

Booking

Booking couldn’t be simpler, check your month and dates in the calendar, then contact us.
